Probably lookin' at some very fine jewelry.
Possible cash hoard.

00:28:29.335 --> 00:28:33.672
Odd marketable securities.
Who knows?

00:28:33.673 --> 00:28:36.008
It's a gem.

00:28:36.009 --> 00:28:38.169
Grab your crowbar.

00:28:39.220 --> 00:28:41.381
Crowbars up.

00:29:40.156 --> 00:29:40.990
Which way?

00:29:40.991 --> 00:29:44.427
We'll go around back to the basement.
Follow me.

00:30:04.097 --> 00:30:06.265
I thought you said
they were gone.

00:30:06.266 --> 00:30:10.303
- They were supposed to leave this morning.
- Let's get out of here.

00:30:46.639 --> 00:30:49.308
We have to use the phone, please.

00:30:49.309 --> 00:30:52.144
It's an emergency.
We really have to make a call.

00:30:52.145 --> 00:30:55.314
Please! Our brother's home alone.

00:30:55.315 --> 00:30:58.650
- Give us the phone!
- Thank you. I'm sorry. Thank you.

00:30:58.651 --> 00:31:01.737
Peter, I'm gonna call the police.
Why don't you book us a flight home.

00:31:01.738 --> 00:31:06.491
Get some change out of here.
Call everybody you know. Oh. Leslie.

00:31:06.492 --> 00:31:09.786
Here's my address book. You and Frank
call everybody who lives on our street.

00:31:09.787 --> 00:31:11.788
Maybe somebody can help us.

00:31:11.789 --> 00:31:16.077
Hello? Hello? Hello?
She'll have to call you back.

00:31:21.007 --> 00:31:25.010
This is ridiculous. Only a wimp
would be hiding under a bed.

00:31:25.011 --> 00:31:29.340
And I can't be a wimp.
I'm the man of the house.

00:31:36.439 --> 00:31:39.517
Hey! I'm not afraid anymore!

00:31:40.777 --> 00:31:44.863
I said, I'm not afraid anymore!

00:31:44.864 --> 00:31:47.900
Do you hear me?
I'm not afraid anymore!

00:32:18.690 --> 00:32:20.732
Village Police Department.

00:32:20.733 --> 00:32:24.403
Hi. Look, I'm calling from Paris.
I have a son who's home alone.

00:32:24.404 --> 00:32:27.906
Our phones are out of order,
so I'd like somebody to go to our house...

00:32:27.907 --> 00:32:29.908
and tell him we're
coming home to get him.

