I told you something's wrong. I knew
he looked at me weird. Why would he run?

00:44:16.908 --> 00:44:21.078
- Maybe he went in the church.
- I'm not goin' in there.

00:44:21.079 --> 00:44:24.031
- Me neither.
- Ah, let's get out of here.

00:44:42.475 --> 00:44:45.803
When those guys come back,
I'll be ready.

00:45:11.296 --> 00:45:14.040
- Did they come back?
- From Paris?

00:45:49.542 --> 00:45:52.544
We'll come back tomorrow.
Maybe they'll be gone by then.

00:45:52.545 --> 00:45:56.833
We'd better get out of here
before somebody sees us.

00:46:25.370 --> 00:46:27.621
Attention! Attention!

00:46:27.622 --> 00:46:31.667
- Look what I have found in "ze" kitchen!
- Frank, those are for later.

00:46:31.668 --> 00:46:33.828
Frank?

00:46:35.046 --> 00:46:39.007
Mes petites enfants,
do you want a little shrimp, eh?

00:46:39.008 --> 00:46:42.344
Oper... Do you speak English?

00:46:42.345 --> 00:46:45.264
Parlez anglais?

00:46:45.265 --> 00:46:47.307
Is there... I mean...

00:46:47.308 --> 00:46:52.354
Est ce qui un person
qui parle anglais?

00:46:52.355 --> 00:46:55.524
- Did you get anybody?
- I'm looking for my son! Do you know where he is?

00:46:55.525 --> 00:47:00.946
I can't find anybody. They've all gone
shopping. Nobody's home for the holidays.

00:47:00.947 --> 00:47:03.115
Never mind. Forget it.

00:47:03.116 --> 00:47:05.284
This is so pointless.

00:47:05.285 --> 00:47:09.121
- What?
- We're here rotting in this apartment.

00:47:09.122 --> 00:47:11.415
Kevin's at home.
Mom's at the airport.

00:47:11.416 --> 00:47:13.792
- So?
- You're not at all worried about Kevin?

00:47:13.793 --> 00:47:15.794
Why should I be?

00:47:15.795 --> 00:47:19.464
He's acted like a jerk too many times,
and this time he caught it in the butt.

00:47:19.465 --> 00:47:24.094
But he's so little and helpless.
Don't you think he's flipped out?

00:47:24.095 --> 00:47:27.389
The little trout can use
a couple of days in the real world.

00:47:27.390 --> 00:47:29.808
You're not worried that something
might happen to him?

00:47:29.809 --> 00:47:32.394
No. For three reasons.

00:47:32.395 --> 00:47:35.147
I'm not that lucky.

00:47:35.148 --> 00:47:37.524
Two: We have smoke detectors.

00:47:37.525 --> 00:47:41.612
And "D": We live in the most boring street
in the United States of America...

00:47:41.613 --> 00:47:46.192
where nothing even remotely dangerous
will ever happen, period.

00:48:13.144 --> 00:48:16.647
- Who is it?
- It's Little Nero's, sir. I have your pizza.

00:48:16.648 --> 00:48:19.942
Leave it on the doorstep
and get the hell outta here.

00:48:19.943 --> 00:48:22.819
Okay.

00:48:22.820 --> 00:48:25.189
Um, well, what about the money?

00:48:26.199 --> 00:48:27.950
What money?

00:48:27.951 --> 00:48:31.453
Well, you have to pay
for your pizza, sir.

00:48:31.454 --> 00:48:33.789
Is that a fact?

00:48:33.790 --> 00:48:36.041
How much do I owe you?

00:48:36.042 --> 00:48:39.537
Uh, that'll be 11.80, sir.

00:48:45.718 --> 00:48:49.255
Keep the change,
ya filthy animal.

00:48:50.932 --> 00:48:52.933
- Cheapskate.
- Hey.

00:48:52.934 --> 00:48:56.854
I'm gonna give you to the count
of 10 to get your ugly...

00:48:56.855 --> 00:49:00.232
yellow, no-good keister
off my property...

00:49:00.233 --> 00:49:02.568
before I pump your guts
full of lead.

00:49:02.569 --> 00:49:04.645
One, two, ten!

00:49:33.433 --> 00:49:36.636
A lovely cheese pizza
just for me.

00:49:39.939 --> 00:49:42.308
To Dallas-Fort Worth.

00:49:45.528 --> 00:49:47.988
We have the $500,
the pocket translator...

00:49:47.989 --> 00:49:50.782
the two first-class seats...
that's an upgrade from your coach...

00:49:50.783 --> 00:49:54.703
- Is that a real Rolex?
- Do you think it is?

00:49:54.704 --> 00:49:57.456
- No.
- But who can tell?

00:49:57.457 --> 00:50:01.543
- I also have a ring.
- That is beautiful!

00:50:01.544 --> 00:50:04.129
Come on. They're boarding.

00:50:04.130 --> 00:50:07.758
This gal has offered us
two first-class tickets if we go Friday.

00:50:07.759 --> 00:50:11.386
Plus a ring, a watch,
a pocket translator, $500 and...

00:50:11.387 --> 00:50:14.223
- The earrings. You love the earrings.
- She's got her own earrings.

00:50:14.224 --> 00:50:16.975
A whole shoe box full of' em.
Dangley ones.

00:50:16.976 --> 00:50:19.061
- Come on, come on.
- No, but...

00:50:19.062 --> 00:50:21.146
I'm desperate.

00:50:21.147 --> 00:50:23.148
I'm begging you.

00:50:23.149 --> 00:50:26.769
From a mother to a mother, please.

00:50:28.071 --> 00:50:30.781
- Oh, Ed.
- Please.

00:50:30.782 --> 00:50:33.651
Oh, all right.

00:50:39.123 --> 00:50:41.250
"Dear Santa Claus.
I got a little sister last year.

00:50:41.251 --> 00:50:43.619
This year I'd rather
have some clay dough."

00:50:57.517 --> 00:50:59.518
I didn't mean it.

00:50:59.519 --> 00:51:02.813
If you come back,
I'll never be a pain in the butt again.

00:51:02.814 --> 00:51:05.975
I promise. Good night.

00:51:25.962 --> 00:51:29.332
♪ I'm dreaming

00:51:29.382 --> 00:51:30.792
♪ Of a white

00:51:31.676 --> 00:51:33.544
♪ Christmas

00:51:33.928 --> 00:51:38.299
♪ Just like the ones I used to know

00:51:40.310 --> 00:51:44.305
♪ Where those treetops glisten

00:51:44.314 --> 00:51:48.142
♪ And children listen

00:51:48.151 --> 00:51:53.398
♪ To hear sleigh bells
♪ In the snow

00:51:53.948 --> 00:51:55.817
♪ The snow

00:52:46.960 --> 00:52:49.461
Are those microwave dinners
any good?

00:52:49.462 --> 00:52:52.999
- I don't know.
- I'll give 'em a whirl.

00:52:57.720 --> 00:53:00.048
For the kids.

00:53:02.183 --> 00:53:04.893
Hold on.
I got a coupon for that.

00:53:04.894 --> 00:53:07.764
It was in the paper this morning.

00:53:11.150 --> 00:53:14.187
- 19.83.
- Okay.

00:53:17.490 --> 00:53:19.817
Are you here all by yourself?

00:53:21.160 --> 00:53:25.330
Ma'am, I'm eight years old.
You think I would be here alone?

00:53:25.331 --> 00:53:27.791
I don't think so.

00:53:27.792 --> 00:53:30.169
- Where's your mom?
- My mom's in the car.

00:53:30.170 --> 00:53:32.671
- And where is your father?
- He's at work.

00:53:32.672 --> 00:53:35.507
- What about your brothers and your sisters?
- I'm an only child.

00:53:35.508 --> 00:53:38.135
- Where do you live?
- I can't tell you that.

00:53:38.136 --> 00:53:41.339
- Why not?
- 'Cause you're a stranger.

00:54:19.219 --> 00:54:23.214
Hello, Kevin!

00:54:24.307 --> 00:54:27.885
Shut up.

00:54:40.698 --> 00:54:42.699
I don't get it.

00:54:42.700 --> 00:54:45.494
I mean, right now it looks
like there's nobody home.

00:54:45.495 --> 00:54:49.164
Last night the place is jumpin'.

00:54:49.165 --> 00:54:53.077
Somethin' ain't right.
Go check it out.

00:55:01.469 --> 00:55:03.512
Now?

00:55:03.513 --> 00:55:05.514
No, tomorrow, egghead. Now!

00:55:05.515 --> 00:55:08.225
Go ahead!

00:55:08.226 --> 00:55:10.636
"Now?"

00:55:27.745 --> 00:55:30.323
Shit.

00:55:31.958 --> 00:55:34.960
- Get the hell outta here.
- All right, Johnny.

00:55:34.961 --> 00:55:38.213
- But what about my money?
- What money?

00:55:38.214 --> 00:55:41.008
Acey said you had
some dough for me.

00:55:41.009 --> 00:55:45.971
- Is that a fact? How much do I owe you?
- Acey said 10%.

00:55:45.972 --> 00:55:51.101
- Too bad Acey ain't in charge no more.
- What do you mean?

00:55:51.102 --> 00:55:54.605
He's upstairs taking a bath.

00:55:54.606 --> 00:55:57.399
He'll call you when he gets out.

00:55:57.400 --> 00:55:59.401
Hey.

00:55:59.402 --> 00:56:02.487
I tell you what
I'm gonna give you, Snakes.

00:56:02.488 --> 00:56:06.450
- Snakes?
- I'm gonna give you to the count of 10...

00:56:06.451 --> 00:56:08.827
to get your ugly, yellow...

00:56:08.828 --> 00:56:13.373
no-good keister off my property
before I pump your guts full of lead.

00:56:13.374 --> 00:56:16.168
All right, Johnny, I'm sorry.
I'm goin'.

00:56:16.169 --> 00:56:19.330
One, two, ten!

00:56:38.358 --> 00:56:41.728
Keep the change,
ya filthy animal.

00:56:45.532 --> 00:56:46.433
What happened?

00:56:46.434 --> 00:56:49.993
I don't know who's in there, but
somebody just got blown away!

00:56:49.994 --> 00:56:50.520
- Huh?

00:56:50.521 --> 00:56:52.621
Somebody beat us to the job.
They're in there!

00:56:52.622 --> 00:56:56.708
Two of' em. They was arguing.
One of' em blew the other one away.

00:56:56.709 --> 00:56:58.502
- Who?
- I don't know.

00:56:58.503 --> 00:57:01.046
I thought I recognized
one of their voices.

00:57:01.047 --> 00:57:04.341
And I know I heard that name
Snakes before.

00:57:04.342 --> 00:57:06.969
Snakes? Snakes, Snakes.

00:57:06.970 --> 00:57:09.179
- I don't know no Snakes.
- Snakes.

00:57:09.180 --> 00:57:11.924
Let's get out of here.

00:57:14.143 --> 00:57:16.895
Hold it, hold it.
Let's wait and see who it is.

00:57:16.896 --> 00:57:18.897
We work this neighborhood too.

00:57:18.898 --> 00:57:21.817
- Yeah.
- Supposin' the cops finger us for a job...

00:57:21.818 --> 00:57:24.903
and they start asking us questions
about a murder in the area.

00:57:24.904 --> 00:57:28.232
Wouldn't it be nice to have
a face to go with their questions?

00:57:29.909 --> 00:57:31.994
That's a good idea.

00:57:31.995 --> 00:57:35.539
Of course it's a good idea.
Snakes?

00:57:35.540 --> 00:57:38.618
He sounded like a snake.

00:57:42.505 --> 00:57:45.716
Everything's full.

00:57:45.717 --> 00:57:47.718
Everything's full?

00:57:47.719 --> 00:57:50.053
I'm very sorry,
but it is Christmas Eve.

00:57:50.054 --> 00:57:52.382
What about another airline?

00:57:57.604 --> 00:58:00.689
Nothing available. May I help you
get a hotel room in the city?

00:58:00.690 --> 00:58:03.009
Tomorrow afternoon we can
get you a flight to Chicago.

00:58:03.010 --> 00:58:04.276
I can't wait that long.

00:58:04.277 --> 00:58:08.898
I'm terribly sorry, ma'am, but we're
doing absolutely everything we can.

00:58:12.869 --> 00:58:16.079
Go ahead. I'm in your way.
You have places to go, people to see.

00:58:16.080 --> 00:58:19.541
You got a ticket there.
That's good. Excuse me. Look.

00:58:19.542 --> 00:58:23.629
I have been awake for almost 60 hours.
I'm tired and I'm dirty.

00:58:23.630 --> 00:58:28.217
I have been from Chicago to Paris
to Dallas to... Where the hell am I?

00:58:28.218 --> 00:58:30.302
Scranton.

00:58:30.303 --> 00:58:33.096
I am trying to get home
to my eight-year-old son!

00:58:33.097 --> 00:58:36.600
And now that I'm this close,
you're telling me it's hopeless?

00:58:36.601 --> 00:58:40.312
- I'm sorry.
- No. No, no, no, no way. This is Christmas!

00:58:40.313 --> 00:58:42.314
The season of perpetual hope!

00:58:42.315 --> 00:58:43.131
Ma'am, if I...

00:58:43.132 --> 00:58:46.235
If I have to get out on
your runway and hitchhike...

00:58:46.236 --> 00:58:48.278
if it costs me everything I own...

00:58:48.279 --> 00:58:51.240
if I have to sell my soul
to the devil himself...

00:58:51.241 --> 00:58:54.493
I am going to get home
to my son.

00:58:54.494 --> 00:58:57.822
Ma'am, if there was anything at
all I could do for you today...

00:58:57.823 --> 00:58:58.747
Do it.

00:58:58.748 --> 00:59:01.458
- Do anything.
- I can get you a hotel room.

00:59:01.459 --> 00:59:03.961
- What?
- Excuse me.

00:59:03.962 --> 00:59:09.800
Can you excuse us for a second? Can I see
you for a second? Please. Excuse us. Come.

00:59:09.801 --> 00:59:13.095
Couldn't help but hearin'
you got a little bit of a dilemma there.

00:59:13.096 --> 00:59:15.806
We got a crisis ourselves.

00:59:15.807 --> 00:59:19.351
Allow me to introduce myself.
Gus Polinski. How are you?

00:59:19.352 --> 00:59:22.972
Polka king of the Midwest?

00:59:25.650 --> 00:59:28.485
The Kenosha Kickers?

00:59:28.486 --> 00:59:30.279
- Hi there.
- Hiya.

00:59:30.280 --> 00:59:33.198
No? That's okay. I thought
you might've recognized...

00:59:33.199 --> 00:59:36.243
Anyways, uh, I had
a few hits a few years ago.

00:59:36.244 --> 00:59:39.739
Uh, that's why, you know...
"Polka, Polka, Polka"?

00:59:42.125 --> 00:59:44.209
No? "Twin Lakes Polka."

00:59:44.210 --> 00:59:47.796
"Yamahoozie Polka,"
a.k.a. "Kiss Me Polka."

00:59:47.797 --> 00:59:50.507
- "Polka Twist."
- These are songs?

00:59:50.508 --> 00:59:54.011
Yeah. Yeah. We...
Some fairly big hits for us.

00:59:54.012 --> 00:59:56.722
- You know, in the early '70s, you know?
- Oh.

00:59:56.723 --> 00:59:59.474
Yeah, we sold
about 623 copies of that.

00:59:59.475 --> 01:00:02.186
- In Chicago?
- No. Sheboygan. Very big in Sheboygan.

01:00:02.187 --> 01:00:04.479
I'm sorry. Did you say
you could help me?

01:00:04.480 --> 01:00:06.690
Anyway, I'm rambling on here.

01:00:06.691 --> 01:00:09.860
Our flight was canceled,
so we gotta drive.

01:00:09.861 --> 01:00:13.530
So, uh, see the guy in the yellow jacket
over there by the Budget sign?

01:00:13.531 --> 01:00:17.367
He's gonna rent us a nice big, uh, van,
and we're gonna drive to Milwaukee.

01:00:17.368 --> 01:00:21.788
I heard you had some problems here, uh, gettin'
to Chicago to see your kid or somethin'?

01:00:21.789 --> 01:00:26.001
Uh, my son. He...
We left and he's there.

01:00:26.002 --> 01:00:30.214
Aw, geez. If you have to get
to Chicago, we'll gladly drive you.

01:00:30.215 --> 01:00:32.549
It's on the way to Milwaukee.

01:00:32.550 --> 01:00:35.302
- You'd give me a ride?
- Sure we will. Why not, you know?

01:00:35.303 --> 01:00:37.930
- You gotta get home and see your kid.
- A ride to Chicago?

01:00:37.931 --> 01:00:39.890
Sure. You know,
it's Christmastime.

01:00:39.891 --> 01:00:42.559
Thank you.
Oh, thank you.

01:00:42.560 --> 01:00:44.937
If you don't mind goin'
with some polka bums.

01:00:44.938 --> 01:00:47.056
No, I'd love to.

01:01:08.586 --> 01:01:11.588
- Hey, Marv, Marv, Marv.
- What?

01:01:11.589 --> 01:01:14.250
Look at this.

01:01:18.596 --> 01:01:23.176
I think we're gettin' scammed
by a "kindygartener."

01:01:53.089 --> 01:01:55.833
Dad, can you come here
and help me?

01:02:00.138 --> 01:02:04.474
Remember that kid we saw
the other day? He lives here.

01:02:04.475 --> 01:02:07.477
Well, if the kid's there,
the parents gotta be.

01:02:07.478 --> 01:02:10.264
He's home alone.

01:02:17.947 --> 01:02:20.365
You gotta be kiddin'.
You wanna come back tonight?

01:02:20.366 --> 01:02:22.367
- Uh-huh.
- Even with the kid here?

01:02:22.368 --> 01:02:24.620
- Uh-huh.
- I don't think that's a good idea.

01:02:24.621 --> 01:02:28.165
That house is the only reason we started
workin' this block in the first place.

01:02:28.166 --> 01:02:31.001
Ever since I laid eyes
on that house, I wanted it.

01:02:31.002 --> 01:02:33.462
So let's take it
one step at a time, okay?

01:02:33.463 --> 01:02:37.049
We'll unload the van. We'll get a bite
to eat. We'll come back about 9:00.

01:02:37.050 --> 01:02:40.052
- This way it's dark then.

01:02:40.053 --> 01:02:43.305
Yeah. Kids are scared
of the dark.

01:02:43.306 --> 01:02:46.225
You're afraid of the dark too, Marv.
You know you are.

01:02:46.226 --> 01:02:49.019
No, I'm not!

01:02:49.020 --> 01:02:51.647
- Yes, you are.
- I'm not, not, not.

01:02:51.648 --> 01:02:56.060
- You are so.
- Mom, where are you?

01:03:09.249 --> 01:03:11.250
Do you play?

01:03:11.251 --> 01:03:13.418
You want to try it?
Go ahead. Try it.

01:03:13.419 --> 01:03:15.796
- Try it. Try it.
- No.

01:03:15.797 --> 01:03:18.041
Okay.

01:03:42.073 --> 01:03:45.617
- Excuse me.
- Yeah?

01:03:45.618 --> 01:03:49.705
- Hey, nice shoes.
- Oh, thanks.

01:03:49.706 --> 01:03:53.417
Is he still here? It's really important
that I see him.

01:03:53.418 --> 01:03:58.797
He's getting in his car. I guess
if you hurry, you can catch him.

01:03:58.798 --> 01:04:03.385
Damn! How low can you get? Givin' Kris
Kringle a parking ticket on Christmas Eve.

01:04:03.386 --> 01:04:06.597
What's next?
Rabies shots for the Easter Bunny?

01:04:06.598 --> 01:04:09.266
Santa, hold on!

01:04:09.267 --> 01:04:11.476
Can I talk to you for a minute?

01:04:11.477 --> 01:04:14.605
If you make it quick. Santa's got
a little get-together he's late for.

01:04:14.606 --> 01:04:16.607
Okay. I know you're not
the real Santa Claus.

01:04:16.608 --> 01:04:20.611
What makes you say that?
Just out of curiosity.

01:04:20.612 --> 01:04:23.322
I'm old enough
to know how it works.

01:04:23.323 --> 01:04:26.491
- All right.
- But I also know that you work for him.

01:04:26.492 --> 01:04:29.620
- And I'd like you to give him a message.
- Shoot.

01:04:29.621 --> 01:04:33.832
I'm Kevin McCallister,
671 Lincoln Boulevard.

01:04:33.833 --> 01:04:36.627
- Do you need the phone number?
- No, that's all right.

01:04:36.628 --> 01:04:38.921
Okay.
This is extremely important.

01:04:38.922 --> 01:04:43.800
Would you please tell him that, instead of
presents this year, I just want my family back.

01:04:43.801 --> 01:04:48.805
No toys. Nothing but Peter,
Kate, Buzz, Megan, Linnie and Jeff.

01:04:48.806 --> 01:04:51.141
And my aunt and my cousins.

01:04:51.142 --> 01:04:54.512
And, if he has time,
my Uncle Frank. Okay?

01:04:56.022 --> 01:04:59.316
Okay. I'll see what I can do.

01:04:59.317 --> 01:05:02.319
- Thanks.
- Wait. Hold on a second.

01:05:02.320 --> 01:05:05.572
My elf took the last of the candy canes
home to her boyfriend.

01:05:05.573 --> 01:05:07.699
- That's okay.
- No, no, no. Don't be silly.

01:05:07.700 --> 01:05:10.827
Everybody who sees Santa
has gotta get... somethin'.

01:05:10.828 --> 01:05:13.121
Here. Hold out
your little paw there.

01:05:13.122 --> 01:05:16.333
There you go.
Don't spoil your dinner.

01:05:16.334 --> 01:05:19.120
I won't. Thanks.

01:05:29.848 --> 01:05:32.592
Son of a...

01:08:28.568 --> 01:08:30.903
Merry Christmas.

01:08:30.904 --> 01:08:32.487
Huh?

01:08:32.488 --> 01:08:34.732
May I sit down?

01:08:45.001 --> 01:08:49.706
That's my granddaughter up there.
The little red-haired girl.

01:08:51.716 --> 01:08:53.509
She's about your age.

01:08:53.510 --> 01:08:55.844
- Do you know her?
- No.

01:08:55.845 --> 01:08:59.014
- You live next to me, don't you?
- Yeah.

01:08:59.015 --> 01:09:03.560
You can say hello when you see me.
You don't have to be afraid.

01:09:03.561 --> 01:09:07.564
There's a lot of things going around
about me, but none of it's true.

01:09:07.565 --> 01:09:09.566
Okay?

01:09:09.567 --> 01:09:11.902
- You been a good boy this year?
- I think so.

01:09:11.903 --> 01:09:14.071
Swear to it?

01:09:14.072 --> 01:09:16.907
- No.
- Yeah, I had a feeling.

01:09:16.908 --> 01:09:20.118
Well, this is the place to be
if you're feeling bad about yourself.

01:09:20.119 --> 01:09:23.121
- It is?
- I think so.

01:09:23.122 --> 01:09:26.034
- Are you feeling bad about yourself?
- No.

01:09:30.088 --> 01:09:32.422
I've been kind of a pain lately.

01:09:32.423 --> 01:09:34.925
I said some things
I shouldn't have.

01:09:34.926 --> 01:09:38.303
I really haven't been
too good this year.

01:09:38.304 --> 01:09:41.265
- Yeah.
- I'm kind of upset about it...

01:09:41.266 --> 01:09:43.517
because I really like my family.

01:09:43.518 --> 01:09:46.144
Even though sometimes
I say I don't.

01:09:46.145 --> 01:09:49.648
Sometimes I even think I don't.
Do you get that?

01:09:49.649 --> 01:09:54.278
I think so. How you feel about
your family is a complicated thing.

01:09:54.279 --> 01:09:57.865
Especially with an older brother.

01:09:57.866 --> 01:10:02.244
Deep down you always love 'em,
but you can forget that you love 'em.

01:10:02.245 --> 01:10:05.038
And you can hurt them,
and they can hurt you.

01:10:05.039 --> 01:10:08.876
And that's not just
because you're young.

01:10:08.877 --> 01:10:12.212
You want to know the real reason
that I'm here right now?

01:10:12.213 --> 01:10:14.214
Sure.

01:10:14.215 --> 01:10:17.968
I came to hear my granddaughter sing,
and I can't come and hear her tonight.

01:10:17.969 --> 01:10:23.682
- You have plans?
- No. I'm not welcome.

01:10:23.683 --> 01:10:27.644
- At church?
- Oh, you're always welcome at church.

01:10:27.645 --> 01:10:30.147
I'm not welcome with my son.

01:10:30.148 --> 01:10:34.943
Years back, before you and
your family moved on the block...

01:10:34.944 --> 01:10:37.529
I had an argument with my son.

01:10:37.530 --> 01:10:41.867
- How old is he?
- Oh, he's grown up.

01:10:41.868 --> 01:10:44.620
We lost our tempers...

01:10:44.621 --> 01:10:47.664
and I said I didn't care
to see him anymore.

01:10:47.665 --> 01:10:52.669
He said the same, and we haven't
spoken to each other since.

01:10:52.670 --> 01:10:55.631
If you miss him,
why don't you call him?

01:10:55.632 --> 01:10:58.425
I'm afraid if I call him,
he won't talk to me.

01:10:58.426 --> 01:11:00.719
How do you know?

01:11:00.720 --> 01:11:03.847
I don't know.
I'm just afraid he won't.

01:11:03.848 --> 01:11:07.643
No offense, but aren't you
a little old to be afraid?

01:11:07.644 --> 01:11:11.271
You can be a little old
for a lot of things.

01:11:11.272 --> 01:11:13.607
You're never too old
to be afraid.

01:11:13.608 --> 01:11:16.485
That's true. I've always
been afraid of our basement.

01:11:16.486 --> 01:11:20.030
It's dark, there's weird stuff
down there, and it smells funny.

01:11:20.031 --> 01:11:23.534
That sort of thing.
It's bothered me for years.

01:11:23.535 --> 01:11:26.036
Basements are like that.

01:11:26.037 --> 01:11:29.039
Then I made myself go down there
to do some laundry...

01:11:29.040 --> 01:11:31.124
and I found out
it's not so bad.

01:11:31.125 --> 01:11:33.544
All this time
I've been worrying about it...

01:11:33.545 --> 01:11:35.879
but if you turn on the lights,
it's no big deal.

01:11:35.880 --> 01:11:40.425
- What's your point?
- My point is you should call your son.

01:11:40.426 --> 01:11:42.594
What if he won't talk to me?

01:11:42.595 --> 01:11:46.056
At least you'll know.
Then you could stop worrying about it...

01:11:46.057 --> 01:11:48.725
and you won't have to be
afraid anymore.

01:11:48.726 --> 01:11:52.396
I don't care how mad I was,
I'd talk to my dad...

01:11:52.397 --> 01:11:54.398
especially around the holidays.

01:11:54.399 --> 01:11:57.651
I don't know.

01:11:57.652 --> 01:12:00.904
Just give it a shot.
For your granddaughter anyway.

01:12:00.905 --> 01:12:04.408
I'm sure she misses you...
and the presents.

01:12:04.409 --> 01:12:06.368
I send her a check.

01:12:06.369 --> 01:12:10.747
I wish my grandparents sent that.
They always send me clothes.

01:12:10.748 --> 01:12:13.750
Last year I got a sweater
with a big bird knitted on it.

01:12:13.751 --> 01:12:17.129
- Oh, that's nice.
- Not for a guy in the second grade.

01:12:17.130 --> 01:12:20.215
You can get beat up
for wearing something like that.

01:12:20.216 --> 01:12:22.426
- Oh?
- Yeah.

01:12:22.427 --> 01:12:26.638
I have a friend who got nailed 'cause there
was a rumor he wore dinosaur pajamas.

01:12:26.639 --> 01:12:30.058
You'd better run along home
where you belong.

01:12:30.059 --> 01:12:32.060
You think about what I said.

01:12:32.061 --> 01:12:33.937
- All right?
- Okay.

01:12:33.938 --> 01:12:38.017
- It was nice talking to you.
- Nice talking to you.

01:12:43.740 --> 01:12:47.117
- What about you?
- Me?

01:12:47.118 --> 01:12:49.244
Yeah. You and your son.

01:12:49.245 --> 01:12:52.623
We'll see what happens.

01:12:52.624 --> 01:12:55.667
Merry Christmas.

01:12:55.668 --> 01:12:57.787
Merry Christmas.

01:13:50.348 --> 01:13:54.552
This is my house.
I have to defend it.

01:15:21.940 --> 01:15:26.018
Okay, we'll check it out first.
We can always come back for the truck.

01:15:32.450 --> 01:15:34.785
How do you wanna go in?

01:15:34.786 --> 01:15:38.330
We'll go to the back door.
Maybe he'll let us in. You never know.

01:15:38.331 --> 01:15:41.993
Yeah. He's a kid.
Kids are stupid.

01:15:43.837 --> 01:15:47.840
Bless this highly nutritious microwavable
macaroni and cheese dinner...

01:15:47.841 --> 01:15:49.967
and the people
who sold it on sale.

01:15:49.968 --> 01:15:52.086
Amen.

01:16:15.743 --> 01:16:18.821
This is it.
Don't get scared now.

01:16:31.926 --> 01:16:34.511
Merry Christmas, little fella.

01:16:34.512 --> 01:16:37.181
We know that you're in there...

01:16:37.182 --> 01:16:40.184
and that you're all alone.

01:16:40.185 --> 01:16:42.895
Yeah, come on, kid. Open up.

01:16:42.896 --> 01:16:46.641
It's Santa Claus and his elf.

01:16:47.859 --> 01:16:50.194
We're not gonna hurt you.

01:16:50.195 --> 01:16:54.239
No, no. We got
some nice presents for you.

01:16:54.240 --> 01:16:57.902
Be a good little fella now
and open the door.

01:17:00.622 --> 01:17:03.498
Shoot!

01:17:03.499 --> 01:17:07.377
What? What? What?

01:17:07.378 --> 01:17:10.506
What? What happened?

01:17:10.507 --> 01:17:14.252
Get that little...

01:17:23.394 --> 01:17:25.763
Hello.

01:17:30.902 --> 01:17:33.445
Yes! Yes!

01:17:33.446 --> 01:17:35.614
The little jerk is armed!

01:17:35.615 --> 01:17:39.618
That's it! That's it! I'm goin' around
the front! You go down the basement!

01:17:39.619 --> 01:17:42.280
That little...

01:18:18.366 --> 01:18:20.610
Ow!

01:18:42.056 --> 01:18:44.467
That smart aleck.

01:20:12.021 --> 01:20:17.067
Oh, boy, that's it, you little...
you little son of a...

01:20:17.068 --> 01:20:20.229
Oh, not this time,
you little brat.

01:20:23.616 --> 01:20:26.201
You little creep, you,
where are you?

01:20:26.202 --> 01:20:30.573
Where are you, you little creep?

01:20:50.101 --> 01:20:54.222
Yes! Yes!
Yes, yes, yes, yes!

01:21:24.761 --> 01:21:27.755
I'll rip his head off!

01:21:33.811 --> 01:21:38.725
You're dead, kid.

01:22:25.572 --> 01:22:28.900
Where are you,
you little creep?

01:22:44.048 --> 01:22:47.877
Harry! I'm comin' in!

01:22:52.307 --> 01:22:54.808
Oh, no, I'm really scared!

01:22:54.809 --> 01:22:57.561
It's too late for you, kid.
We're already in the house.

01:22:57.562 --> 01:23:01.732
- We're gonna get you!
- Okay. Come and get me.

01:23:01.733 --> 01:23:04.477
Why, you...

01:23:08.740 --> 01:23:11.401
Now you're dead!

01:23:35.475 --> 01:23:38.177
I'm gonna kill that kid!

01:23:52.450 --> 01:23:55.619
- Marv!
- Harry?

01:23:55.620 --> 01:23:57.746
Why the hell'd
you take your shoes off?

01:23:57.747 --> 01:24:01.075
Why the hell are you
dressed like a chicken?

01:24:02.293 --> 01:24:06.247
I'm up here, you morons!
Come and get me!

01:24:08.258 --> 01:24:12.128
You guys give up,
or are you thirsty for more?

01:24:21.646 --> 01:24:24.189
- Heads up!
- Huh?

01:24:24.190 --> 01:24:27.484
Don't worry, Marv. I'll get him for you.

01:24:27.485 --> 01:24:31.113
Ow!

01:24:31.114 --> 01:24:34.692
Yes!

01:24:38.663 --> 01:24:41.498
He's only a kid, Harry.
We can take him.

01:24:41.499 --> 01:24:43.584
- Aw, shut up, will ya!
- Oh!

01:24:43.585 --> 01:24:46.670
- What is it?
- You're missin' some teeth.

01:24:46.671 --> 01:24:51.008
Where? It's my gold tooth.
My gold tooth! I'll kill him!

01:24:51.009 --> 01:24:54.511
I'll kill him!

01:24:54.512 --> 01:24:57.389
You bomb me
with one more can, kid...

01:24:57.390 --> 01:25:01.761
and I'll snap off your cojones
and boil them in motor oil!

01:25:04.022 --> 01:25:06.231
911 Emergency.

01:25:06.232 --> 01:25:09.067
Help. My house is being robbed.

01:25:09.068 --> 01:25:13.856
My address is 656 Lincoln Boulevard.
My name's Murphy.

01:25:16.367 --> 01:25:19.036
Watch it. You never know
what's up there.

01:25:19.037 --> 01:25:22.115
There he is!

01:25:23.041 --> 01:25:26.251
Ah! I got ya!

01:25:26.252 --> 01:25:29.713
I got him, Harry!
Harry, I got him!

01:25:29.714 --> 01:25:32.883
Harry, get up! Give me a hand!

01:25:32.884 --> 01:25:37.179
Ow! I got him!

01:25:37.180 --> 01:25:40.766
Harry, help me! Get up!

01:25:40.767 --> 01:25:43.720
I got him!

01:26:22.058 --> 01:26:26.979
- What are you doing, Marv?
- Harry, don't move.

01:26:26.980 --> 01:26:31.066
- Marv?
- Don't... move!

01:26:31.067 --> 01:26:34.562
Marv, what are you doing?
Marv...

01:26:37.448 --> 01:26:41.118
Did I get him?
Did I get him?

01:26:41.119 --> 01:26:43.579
Where is it?
Where is it?

01:26:43.580 --> 01:26:46.832
Never mind did you get it!
How do you like it? Huh?

01:26:46.833 --> 01:26:50.828
You jerk! Get that kid!
Go on! Get the kid!

01:26:54.007 --> 01:26:57.509
Whoa! Whoa!

01:26:57.510 --> 01:27:01.096
Whoa! Whoa!

01:27:01.097 --> 01:27:04.425
Whoa! Whoa!

01:27:16.779 --> 01:27:18.989
Where'd he go?

01:27:18.990 --> 01:27:21.158
Maybe he committed suicide.

01:27:21.159 --> 01:27:23.368
Down here, you big horse's ass!

01:27:23.369 --> 01:27:26.455
Come and get me
before I call the police!

01:27:26.456 --> 01:27:28.707
- Let's get him!
- Wait. Wait.

01:27:28.708 --> 01:27:30.792
That's just what
he wants us to do...

01:27:30.793 --> 01:27:34.379
us to go back downstairs through
his fun house so we get all tore up.

01:27:34.380 --> 01:27:37.674
- He's gonna call the cops!
- He's not callin' the... From a tree house?

01:27:37.675 --> 01:27:39.676
Come on.

01:27:39.677 --> 01:27:42.054
- Out the window?
- Yeah.

01:27:42.055 --> 01:27:44.848
- I'm not goin' out the window.
- Why? Are you scared, Marv?

01:27:44.849 --> 01:27:47.635
Are you afraid?
Come on. Get out here.

01:27:52.023 --> 01:27:54.142
Come on.

01:27:57.529 --> 01:27:58.273
Come on!

01:28:05.870 --> 01:28:08.539
Come on.
Keep goin'. Keep goin'.

01:28:08.540 --> 01:28:11.583
- Let's go back, Harry.
- Shut up!

01:28:11.584 --> 01:28:14.920
Whoa. Whoa. Whoa.

01:28:14.921 --> 01:28:17.957
Shut it, Marv!

01:28:20.218 --> 01:28:23.220
Hey, guys, check this out.

01:28:23.221 --> 01:28:26.098
Go back! Go back!

01:28:26.099 --> 01:28:27.800
- Go back.
- Okay.

01:28:51.875 --> 01:28:57.038
There he goes! There he is!
Get out of the way, you dope!

01:29:14.439 --> 01:29:19.276
- There he is!
- Hey, I'm calling the cops.

01:29:19.277 --> 01:29:22.279
Wait, wait, wait, wait.
He wants us to follow him.

01:29:22.280 --> 01:29:24.607
I got a better idea.
Come on.

01:29:41.341 --> 01:29:45.802
Hiya, pal.
We outsmarted you this time.

01:29:45.803 --> 01:29:48.965
Get over here!

01:29:52.310 --> 01:29:54.436
What are we
gonna do to him, Harry?

01:29:54.437 --> 01:29:58.941
We'll do exactly what he did to us.
I'm gonna burn his head with a blowtorch.

01:29:58.942 --> 01:30:01.151
Then we can smash his face
with an iron!

01:30:01.152 --> 01:30:05.155
I'd like to slap him right in the face
with a paint can maybe.

01:30:05.156 --> 01:30:07.783
Or shove a nail through his foot.

01:30:07.784 --> 01:30:11.237
I'm gonna bite off every one
of these little fingers one at a time.

01:30:19.629 --> 01:30:23.166
Come on.
Let's get you home.

01:30:44.696 --> 01:30:49.067
Wow. This is great.

01:30:51.536 --> 01:30:54.496
Nice move... always leaving
the water running.

01:30:54.497 --> 01:30:57.909
Now we know each and
every house that you've hit.

01:31:00.670 --> 01:31:04.423
Hey, you know, we've been looking
for you two guys for a long time.

01:31:04.424 --> 01:31:07.509
- Yeah.
- Well, remember, we're the Wet Bandits.

01:31:07.510 --> 01:31:11.722
- Wet Bandits. W-E-T...
- Shut up! Get in the car!

01:31:11.723 --> 01:31:14.683
Hey, come on. Come on.

01:31:14.684 --> 01:31:17.220
- Hands off the head, pal!
- Come on!

01:32:12.742 --> 01:32:15.410
I'm a bad parent.
I'm a bad parent.

01:32:15.411 --> 01:32:18.455
You're not. You know, you're beating
yourself up there, you know.

01:32:18.456 --> 01:32:21.124
Come on. This happens.
These things happen. You know, you...

01:32:21.125 --> 01:32:24.628
Gee, you wanna talk about bad parents?
Look at... Look at us.

01:32:24.629 --> 01:32:29.132
I mean, we're on the road 48, 49 weeks out of the year.
We hardly see our families.

01:32:29.133 --> 01:32:32.636
Uh, Joe over there... Gosh, you know, he...

01:32:32.637 --> 01:32:35.472
He forgets his kids' names
half the time.

01:32:35.473 --> 01:32:39.309
Ziggy over there... He doesn't even...
He's never even met his kid.

01:32:39.310 --> 01:32:43.105
Eddie... Let's just hope none
of them write a book about him.

01:32:43.106 --> 01:32:48.144
Tell me, have you ever gone on vacation
and left your child home?

01:32:50.822 --> 01:32:52.990
No.

01:32:52.991 --> 01:32:56.535
But I did leave one
at a funeral parlor once.

01:32:56.536 --> 01:32:58.829
Yeah, it was...
it was terrible too.

01:32:58.830 --> 01:33:02.249
You know, I was all distraught and
everything. You know, the wife and I...

01:33:02.250 --> 01:33:06.336
we left the little tyke
there in the funeral parlor all day.

01:33:06.337 --> 01:33:10.340
All day. You know, and we went back
at night when we came to our senses.

01:33:10.341 --> 01:33:13.969
And there he was. Apparently he was
there alone all day with a corpse.

01:33:13.970 --> 01:33:16.680
- Oh!
- Whew, yeah. He was okay, you know.

01:33:16.681 --> 01:33:21.685
After six, seven weeks, you know, he
came around and started talking again.

01:33:21.686 --> 01:33:26.231
But he's okay. You know, they get over it.
Kids are resilient like that.

01:33:26.232 --> 01:33:29.067
- Maybe we shouldn't talk about this.
- Well, you brought it up.

01:33:29.068 --> 01:33:32.313
- I was just trying to cheer you up.
- Well, I'm sorry I did.

01:33:58.014 --> 01:34:00.091
Mom?

01:34:04.479 --> 01:34:06.556
Mom?

01:34:09.776 --> 01:34:12.729
Mom?

01:34:58.283 --> 01:35:02.528
Kevin? Kevin!

01:35:33.318 --> 01:35:35.812
Merry Christmas, sweetheart.

01:35:44.829 --> 01:35:47.740
Oh, Kevin, I'm so sorry.

01:36:07.101 --> 01:36:09.353
Where is everybody else?

01:36:09.354 --> 01:36:13.524
Oh, baby, they couldn't come.
They wanted to so much, but...

01:36:13.525 --> 01:36:18.195
I didn't fall asleep in the back of the cab
and drool all over you, did I?

01:36:18.196 --> 01:36:20.572
- I don't drool.
- You guys, would you shut up!

01:36:20.573 --> 01:36:24.034
Come on, you guys, it's Christmas.
Kevin! Kevin, Kevin, my boy!

01:36:24.035 --> 01:36:26.036
- Oh, my God!
- Kevin, how are ya?

01:36:26.037 --> 01:36:28.038
- Merry Christmas.
- Hi, Mom.

01:36:28.039 --> 01:36:30.874
Good to see you. Ah, you're all right.
I love you. You okay?

01:36:30.875 --> 01:36:33.703
- Yeah.
- Hey, Kev.

01:36:35.588 --> 01:36:39.258
It's pretty cool that
you didn't burn the place down.

01:36:39.259 --> 01:36:43.178
Thanks, Buzz.

01:36:43.179 --> 01:36:46.181
Wait a minute.
How did you guys get home?

01:36:46.182 --> 01:36:49.601
Oh, we took the morning flight. Remember?
The one you didn't want to wait for.

01:36:49.602 --> 01:36:52.396
Oh, no.
Oh, thank you.

01:36:52.397 --> 01:36:54.398
- Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas.

01:36:54.399 --> 01:36:56.981
Someone has to find an open store.
We don't have milk.

01:36:56.982 --> 01:36:58.669
I went shopping yesterday.

01:37:00.864 --> 01:37:02.739
You? Shopping?

01:37:02.740 --> 01:37:05.860
I got some milk, eggs
and fabric softener.

01:37:07.203 --> 01:37:09.663
- What?
- No kiddin'?

01:37:09.664 --> 01:37:13.876
What a funny guy. What else did
you do while we were away?

01:37:13.877 --> 01:37:16.954
Just hung around.

01:37:19.591 --> 01:37:21.842
You guys,
put the stuff upstairs.

01:37:21.843 --> 01:37:25.762
You went shopping? He doesn't know how
to tie his shoe, and he's going shopping?

01:37:25.763 --> 01:37:28.716
- Buzz, forget it.
- This is not the Kevin I knew.

01:37:51.956 --> 01:37:54.492
Honey, what's this?

01:38:51.933 --> 01:38:55.762
Kevin!
What did you do to my room?

